    "body": "I like the [Dafny](https://github.com/Microsoft/dafny) syntax for loop invariants. Something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nuint x = 1;\r\nuint y = 0;\r\n\r\nfor (uint i = 0; i < 100; i++) \r\n    invariant x % 2 == 1\r\n    invariant y % 2 == 0\r\n{\r\n    x = x + y;\r\n    y = y + 2;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// postcondition of loop:\r\nassert x % 2 == 1;\r\n```",
