    "created_at": "2019-06-26T11:39:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-06-26T11:39:08Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The way to think about a loop invariant like this is that it should be true every time the loop condition is checked. So in the `for` loop example above, every time `i < 100` is evaluated (no matter whether it comes back true or false), the invariant should be true.\r\n\r\nSo even if the loop is executed 0 times, the condition is still checked once, so yes, the loop invariant must be true.",
